My final post from my week with @TiffanyandCo ~ This trip was unforgettable and after experiencing the full journey of a Tiffany diamond, from traceable sourcing, to investing in local communities, and their sustainability efforts, I‚Äôve grown to appreciate this brand so much more. Wearing #TiffanyAndCo
Sharing is caring ü¶í

We spent the second half of our @TiffanyAndCo adventure surrounded by crystal clear blues in Mauritius! Upon arrival we had a helicopter waiting for us at the airport to fly us to our hotel, it was so beautiful seeing the island from above. The first couple of days we enjoyed some down time and took a boat out for the day with a few locals to learn more about the Mauritian culture and soak up some sun. By day three we continued our journey by going behind the scenes of a Tiffany diamond polishing workshop. It was inspiring to learn about the positive impact and how much individual craftsmanship goes into finalising these diamonds. I spent the last part of the day polishing up a diamond myself which was a really cool experience! #TiffanyAndCo

A few weeks ago I took part in a trip with @TiffanyandCo to experience the journey of a Tiffany diamond. Starting in Antwerp, we visited a Tiffany diamond grading facility where we went behind the scenes to discover exactly what goes into the early stages of evaluating a rough diamond. Not only did we learn about the grading process, but also about the sustainable sourcing and traceability of every Tiffany stone which is so important to promote social and environmental responsibility. 
We also had the chance to explore Antwerp, as a chocolate lover the highlight of the city was indulging myself in as much famous Belgium chocolate as I could find üòã #TiffanyandCo

Throw back thurs to when I spent a week cruisin' Italy and Greece with @theyachtweek! This was one of my fav days when we zipped around Salina on these retro Italian bikes ü§ôüèΩ Bookings just opened for 2018 so if you wanna do this trip or check out the itinerary I did click my bio link! ‚ö°Ô∏è#TheYachtWeek

Swipe across to check out 7 of my favourite pics from my Namibia trip with @Landrover!‚ö°Ô∏è This trip was so unique and incomparable to anything I've done before. It was amazing to experience the unique landscapes of Namibia from the drivers seat. Not only did I experience diverse parts of a new country, but I learned new off road driving skills (the best part was cruising down the beach as you may remember from my stories!)
We got off the beaten track away from the tourist crowds whilst at the same time staying in luxurious different lodges each night.
This trip was fast paced and we saw so much in just one week - the Land Rover experience was truly the best way to see the country and get most out of the time I had.

Highlights: ~ N/a'an wildlife sanctuary where we went for a walk with 2 rescued cheetahs!
~ 'Glamping' under the stars in Spitzkoppe, surrounded by an insane Mars like landscape.
~ Quad biking in Swakopmund, home to the famous dunes by the ocean.
~ Sleeping in the middle of the Namib desert for 2 nights where we star gazed with their in house astronomer (we rigged the camera to his telescope to get that moon shot!)
~ Waking up early to walk amongst the Sossusvlei dunes and the dead trees.

#LandRoverExperience #Discovery #AdventureTravel #Landrover #Spon üëåüèæ

node.text: This is Milly, a baby kangaroo orphan! Sadly her mum was hit by a car and found dead on the side of the road. It's not uncommon for baby kangaroos to survive in their mums pouches but they're often undiscovered for days - in Milly's case, a passerby stopped and checked her mothers pouch. She's now loved and looked after at an amazing kangaroo sanctuary in the Northern Territory @AusOutbackNT #NTaustralia

2015, words cannot describe. It's been an endless adventure that's for sure! I watched the sun rise from the top of Adams peak in Sri Lanka, drove an auto rickshaw 1000km across India, kicked back in the Maldives, jumped down waterfalls in Bali, gambled in Vegas, experienced the Loi Krathong festival in Thailand, swam with whale sharks in the Philippines, island hopped around Greece, camped out in the Wadi Rum desert, got ambushed by lemurs in Madagascar, ate crepes under the Eiffel Tower, bought a motor bike older than me and road tripped across Vietnam, and most importantly I made some life long friends along the way. I'm so stoked and never been more excited for a new year, I can't wait to share it with you guys! 
Wishing you all the best for 2016, follow your passion and chase your dreams, this is your world and anything is possible! 
Next stop - Bangkok!
Rolling in at 7am - Thailand, there's a reason I visit this country countless times. Tomorrow I'm taking a one way flight back into Bangkok, starting the new year with a new adventure!

Temple run - 85km north from the hustle and bustle of Bangkok is the ancient city of Ayutthaya. I spent the day hanging out at this beautiful Buddhist temple, bathing in the sun and eating ice cream. Wat Chaiwatthanaram, Thailand.

This kid loved seeing himself on camera, his little face lit up when I played back the video - one of the many faces I filmed whilst road tripping across northern Vietnam. I'm now back in Thailand for the next four days before flying home for Christmas! üì∑ @matthew_parent

I've spent the last two days driving 435km up into the mountains from Ha Long Bay to Sapa. I'm finally here and it's still as beautiful (and cold) as I remember. I'll be spending the next 5 days filming for a short montage which will be ready for your viewing pleasure before Christmas. On another note, where to spend new year? üì∑ @stefan_haworth
